From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] privacy: enable HTTPS-only mode by default

Sets the HTTPS-Only mode pref to enabled on first launch. When enabled,
Chromium's HttpsOnlyModeNavigationThrottle intercepts HTTP navigations
and either upgrades them to HTTPS or shows an interstitial warning if
the HTTPS version is unavailable.

Chromium default: disabled
Fennec default:   enabled (HTTPS_ONLY_MODE_ENABLED = 1)

Users can disable globally or add per-site exceptions via:
  Settings → Privacy → HTTPS-only mode

This patch sets the pref default. The HTTPS-Only mode infrastructure
is already present in Chromium; this is a one-line default flip.

PILLAR: Privacy
JOURNAL: none — this patch prevents unencrypted navigations.
         The HTTPS upgrade itself generates no extra network calls.

---
 chrome/browser/ssl/https_only_mode_policy_handler.cc | 6 ++++--
 chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc              | 5 +++++
 2 files changed, 9 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
index 7a8b9c0d..3e4f5d6a 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
@@ -430,6 +430,11 @@ void ProfileImpl::RegisterProfilePrefs(
+  // Fennec: enable HTTPS-Only mode by default.
+  // HttpsOnlyModeService reads kHttpsOnlyModeEnabled.
+  // Values: 0 = disabled, 1 = enabled, 2 = enabled+strict (no fallback)
+  registry->RegisterIntegerPref(
+      prefs::kHttpsOnlyModeEnabled,
+      1,  // HTTPS_ONLY_MODE_ENABLED — warn, allow HTTP bypass
+      user_prefs::PrefRegistrySyncable::SYNCABLE_PREF);
 }

diff --git a/chrome/browser/ssl/https_only_mode_policy_handler.cc b/chrome/browser/ssl/https_only_mode_policy_handler.cc
index 5e6f7a8b..9c0d1e2f 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/ssl/https_only_mode_policy_handler.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/ssl/https_only_mode_policy_handler.cc
@@ -38,8 +38,8 @@ bool HttpsOnlyModePolicyHandler::CheckPolicySettings(
   // Chromium default is disabled; Fennec flips the pref default in
-  // ProfileImpl but leaves this handler logic unchanged.
+  // ProfileImpl. This handler reads whatever the user has set; the
+  // Fennec default (enabled) propagates naturally from the pref default.
   return true;
 }
